in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B983CFBE7FC14FBDC" authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[863,960,1098,1124]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Scallasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B983CFBE7FC14FBDC" box="[863,960,1098,1124]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Scallasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
relies on Grebenjuk’s (1975) figures of the maxilliped 3, pereopod 3 and telson, and to a lesser extent the major cheliped and uropod. The proximal bifid meral spine on the female major cheliped is similar to that seen in male 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9830FB3EFC30FB14" baseAuthorityName="Ngoc-Ho" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[851,996,1170,1197]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Scallasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caledonica">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9830FB3EFC30FB14" box="[851,996,1170,1197]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">S. caledonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9F74FB3EFB57FB14" authority="Komai &amp; Poore &amp; Fujita, 2020" authorityName="Komai &amp; Poore &amp; Fujita" authorityYear="2020" box="[1047,1155,1171,1197]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Scallasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inermis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9F74FB3EFB57FB14" box="[1047,1155,1171,1197]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">S. inermis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9FEBFB3FFB10FB14" bold="true" box="[1160,1220,1170,1196]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26D40273465E46B9FEBFB3FFB10FB14" box="[1160,1220,1170,1196]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The structure of the eyestalk appears unique in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9ADCFB1BFDF4FB68" authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[447,544,1206,1232]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Scallasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9ADCFB1BFDF4FB68" box="[447,544,1206,1232]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Scallasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the terminal location of the cornea and the lack of a distomesial projection. No dorsal plate, facial spiniform setae or margin tooth were figured on the uropod – we assume they were overlooked.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B95214E3465E46B9BA4FB53FC0EFA74" blockId="18.[151,1437,881,1485]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB5CBF3465E46B9BA4FB53FE4CFAA0" author="Dworschak, P. C." box="[199,408,1278,1304]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" pagination="305 - 307" refId="ref11217" refString="Dworschak, P. C. (2007) Thalassinideans shrimps of New Caledonia. In: Payri, C. E. &amp; Richer de Forges, B. (Eds.), Documents Scientifiques et Techniques. II 7. Compendium of Marine Species of New Caledonia. 2 eme Edition. IRD, Noumea, pp. 305 - 307." type="book chapter" year="2007">Dworschak (2007)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9926FB53FCE6FAA0" authorityName="Grebenjuk" authorityYear="1975" box="[581,818,1278,1304]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinae">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9926FB53FCE6FAA0" box="[581,818,1278,1304]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Callianassa tonkinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9F36FB53FA84FAA0" baseAuthorityName="Bate" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1109,1360,1278,1304]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amboinae">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9F36FB53FA84FAA0" box="[1109,1360,1278,1304]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Callianassa amboinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB5CBF3465E46B9E3DFB53FF36FA84" author="Sakai, K." pageId="18" pageNumber="419" pagination="1431 - 1467" refId="ref11995" refString="Sakai, K. (2010) Callianassoidea from the Gulf of Tonkin and the Red sea, in the Zoological Museum of Moscow University (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana, 83, 1431 - 1467. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 001121610 X 538174" type="journal article" year="2010">Sakai (2010)</bibRefCitation>
referred the material identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9912FA8FFCB4FA84" authorityName="Grebenjuk" authorityYear="1975" box="[625,864,1314,1340]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinae">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9912FA8FFCB4FA84" box="[625,864,1314,1340]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Callianassa tonkinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Andaman Sea by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB5CBF3465E46B9FFDFA8FFAE5FA84" author="Sakai, K." box="[1182,1329,1314,1340]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" pagination="461 - 532" refId="ref11936" refString="Sakai, K. (2002) Callianassidae (Decapoda, Thalassinidea) in the Andaman Sea, Thailand. Phuket Marine Biological Center Special Publication, 23, 461 - 532." type="journal article" year="2002">Sakai (2002)</bibRefCitation>
to a new taxon 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9BBEFAEAFE3CFAD8" authorityName="Sakai, 2010:" authorityYear="1438" box="[221,488,1350,1376]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Trypaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andamaniensis">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9BBEFAEAFE3CFAD8" box="[221,488,1350,1376]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Trypaea andamaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB5CBF3465E46B9A94FAEBFD41FAD9" author="Sakai, K." box="[503,661,1350,1377]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" pagination="1117 - 1137" refId="ref12091" refString="Sakai, K. (2011 b) Callianassidae (II) and Upogebiidae from the Gulf of Tonkin and the Red Sea, in the Zoological Museum of Moscow University (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana, 84, 1117 - 1137. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 001121611 X 586684" type="journal article" year="2011">Sakai (2011b)</bibRefCitation>
identified specimens from the Red Sea, 
<quantity id="4CD28CAB3465E46B9F3CFAE8FB4FFAD9" box="[1119,1179,1349,1377]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" unit="m" value="53.0">53 m</quantity>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F33D61DE3465E46B9FB5FAEBFAECFAD8" box="[1238,1336,1350,1376]" name="Vietnam" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<quantity id="4CD28CAB3465E46B9E27FAEBFAA9FAD9" box="[1348,1405,1350,1377]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" unit="m" value="46.0">46 m</quantity>
as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9BC7FAC6FED4FA3C" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[164,256,1387,1412]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Trypaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9BC7FAC6FED4FA3C" box="[164,256,1387,1412]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Trypaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A5ACD3465E46B9A70FAC7FEA7FA3C" authorityName="Grebenjuk" authorityYear="1975" box="[275,371,1386,1412]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianassa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinae">
<emphasis id="B95EFD5C3465E46B9A70FAC7FEA7FA3C" box="[275,371,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">tonkinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The Red Sea is far west of other records of this genus but we were unable to examine this material. Grebenyuk’s 
<typeStatus id="54919FEC3465E46B9A15FA22FE65FA11" box="[374,433,1423,1449]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">types</typeStatus>
are apparently lost; they were not found in the Zoological Museum of the Moscow State University where Grebenyuk worked (I. Marin, pers. comm. 
<date id="FF94078E3465E46B9821FA1FFC1AFA74" box="[834,974,1458,1485]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" value="2020-01-26">26 Jan 2020</date>
).
</paragraph>
